	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				All the basic crap aside, Halfling Warriors are fairly badass.  I am going to have to argue with some of the earlier posts.  Dex and Agi are THE most important stats for warriors.  They will have an effect on anything you do combatwise, from getting better at skills to hitting with weapons, getting hit less, getting hit for less damage, doing more attacks, the list goes on.  Also keep in mind that adding the points to Str and Sta that you could have added to Dex and Agi, you're going to ruin the reasoning behind making a halfling warrior.  Sure, you can carry a little bit more....yay.  Sure, you hit for one/two/few more hps per hit, but you're going to get WAY more attacks with higher  dex and agi.  I have done massive research on classes and races and all the various combos thereof and have come to the conclusion that Halfling Warrior is certainly among the best.  With the previous being mentioned, you also have access to no experience penalites and the misty thicket.<BR>
The guards in Misty are the most amazing guards I've seen on the game yet.  They may not be hardcore hitters, but they sure as hell do their job of attacking anything they see harmful to the thicket.<BR>
<BR>
My oppinion of your freshly created, naked stats should be something like this:<BR>
<BR>
Str: 90<BR>
Sta: 90<BR>
Dex: 100<BR>
Agi: 100<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
