	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I am also a halfling warrior on brell serilis. When i decided to start a warrior many of my friends in rl and eq said that i should start a barb or troll depending on whether i cared about KoS or not. However i decided to play a halfling for a number of reasons :<BR>
1. They have pretty good all around stats, best agility, best dexterity, and ok strength and stamina.<BR>
2. They are KoS only with the iksar (very nice to have everyone love you : )<BR>
3. I LOVE being short.<BR>
4. Misty is THE best newbie zone in the game and u can stay there until lvl 10 if u want.<BR>
<BR>
Personally i got very lucky with equip. I got an exe axe from a friend, bought a full set of crafted, a TBC for 1hs, two jagged bands, two +45hp rings, and a skull shaped barbute.<BR>
I dumped most of my points into str in the begining for 3 reasons, first the agi and dex are already good, second you only get 1 hp per stamina in the beginning, and last str is THE most important attribute as a warrior.<BR>
<BR>
Karlin lvl 7 halfling warrior Brell Serilis (the best server)
				</font>
